{
  "texts": [
    "The Psychonomic Society, a preeminent society for the experimental study of cognition, was founded in 1959 and their publishing program was started by Clifford T. Morgan in 1964 (19).",
    "Morgan was an academic who became independently wealthy through the sale of his textbook Introduction to Psychology.",
    "Morgan owned Psychonomic Press and started publishing the journal Psychonomic Science in 1964.",
    "This was followed by Psychonomic Monograph Supplements in 1965 and Perception & Psychophysics in 1966.",
    "In 1967, Morgan gifted the three journals to the Psychonomic Society."
  ]
}